Inflation, in Europe, slipped into the food
The accelerated inflation, measured in the euro zone, is due mainly to the rapid increase in the price of food.
In November, the rise in prices, in 13 countries of the euro zone, has been more important in relation to the forecasts, after a rate of inflation of 2.6% in October, an annual inflation of 3.1% has been recorded, pointed out the office of the statistics of the European Community located in Luxembourg.
The official predictions have indicated that 3%, announced Bloomberg.
In contrast to the American, British and Canadian central banks, the European Central Bank (ECB) has not lower the rate of Director in saying that the reduction of the intérets, with the growth of the prices of the premieres and the fall in the rate of unemployment, would lead to the generation of an inflationary spiral.
The ECB would wish to maintain the rate of inflation below but close to two percent.
According to one analyst, it is wrestling 22 for the ECB: "It is necessary to dissuade" inflation in order not to have any more has to intervene on this subject later.
In Germany, the rate of inflation of 3.3% is a record in the course of these twelve years and in Spain, it went up has 4.1.
Inflation in the euro zone has taken off because of the rapid rise in the price of food and energy.
The dimensions of the terms of the cereals market has increased by 88% and the course of soya has also reached its highest value since 1973.
The price of food oil and dairy products also considerably in 2007.
This year, the world price of oil has risen 52% and, last month, a barrel of oil coutait almost 100 dollars.
According to the ECB, in 2008, the rate of inflation will cross, this year, 2.5% but, in 2009, it will go down has 1.9.
According to the analysis, the rate of inflation over 12 months remains around 3%, however, the 3 to 4 months old, the annual average rate will be 2.1%.
In the same time, they expect this that the ECB reduces the director twice in 2008.
Gallup indicates a government crisis
After a long stagnation, the number of supporters of the Fidesz (alliance of young democrats) has increased significantly at the beginning of December, so since 2002, it currently has the greatest number of people, while Gallup survey) (Institute has never seen before such a weak Socialist support, namely 13%.
For the voters, the difference is, because of the greatest determination of the voters of the opposition, the support of more than two thirds (71%) against the support of a cinquieme (20%) for the mszp (the Hungarian Socialist Party).
According to opinion poll, MDF (forum of the Hungarian Democrats) and the szdsz (alliance of free democrats) are below the threshold of Members of Parliament: their support is two percent in the whole population.
On the voters some to go to vote, the number of supporters of the two parties has increased of 1%.
The economic climate has continued to deteriorate in relation to the previous point the lowest, the proportion of those who have judged that the economic situation of the country was particularly serious has never been so high, it amounts has 41% and according to 46% supplementary the situation is serious enough.
After the most optimistic of spring and summer, families are again more pessimistic about their situation.
For the next year, the majority of the population is a worsening and only a dixieme envisages an improvement of the situation.
In December last year, 71% of the people polled, namely a majority ever seen during the previous surveys of Gallup, judged that the Prime Minister did his job rather badly as well.
13% polling trust or a lot of trust in Ferenc Gyurcsány while 38% support Viktor orbán.
54% do not trust at all with the Prime Minister and 27% to the President of the Fidesz.
One of the indicators of the change in the political situation is the proportion of the company thinking that the dissatisfaction with respect to the Prime Minister, can be addressed without a change of government.
Whereas after the riots of last October, 35% polling hoped that the government and Prime Minister remain in office, currently this rate is only 20%; the simple majority (33%) estimates that the behaviour of new elections would be the solution to this situation.
The question regarding the intention to vote, 60 percent polling reply that they would certainly vote and the 20% supplementary say that they would probably vote.
To make the comparison, for an "legislative elections to organize next Sunday," only 55 percent polling would certainly and 15% supplementary would probably. In accordance with the actual intentions, the result of the referendum does not make any doubt.
74% of people would say no to the registration fees in higher education, 79% would say, not at the expense of consultation and 84% would say no to the subsistence expenses hospital.
When we look at only the proportions among the people who have expressed their intention to vote in the referendum, respectively 81, 84 and 89% of the voters would reject the introduction of registration fees, expenses of consultation and subsistence expenses hospital.
