Many hospitals do the economy on the disinfectants
This year, more than a thousand infections, caused by the incorrect use of antibiotics, have been recorded in the hospitals.
The hygienic conditions of hospitals, the insufficient number of beds, the surmenage medical personnel do not help has to block the infections, maintains the doctor in leader of the national centre of epidemiology.
Many hospitals do as the economy on the disinfectants
It is no longer an infection mrsa has been diagnosed in the service of the hospital.
The bacteria resistant to antibiotics has been detected on a man hospital following a serious accident.
The patient has been isolated.
At the beginning of the year a similar infection occurred in the same place.
The casualty of a serious accident of car is out of the hospital but shortly after it has to go back there because of an infection mrsa and, since then, the doctors have not been able to make an important operation because of the bacterium which lies in its organization.
Up to 10 December of this year, 1 094 infections generated by an agent have been declared in the national system of monitoring, pointed out to böröcz, doctor in leader of the national centre of epidemiology.
That is to say that it is the number of infections caused by an agent that has actually been recorded in the hospitals and for the rest we do not have any information.
Approximately two thirds of infections (683 infections) have been caused by the mrsa, in other words by the resistant to the méthicilline-oxacilline.
A third of the people are carriers of the bacterium of aureus staphylococcus (his) in their noses it without a disease.
The infections caused by his (such as throat infections, cutaneous infections, traumatic infections) respond well to antibiotics, they are easily curable.
However, if the antibiotics are used in an excessive or inappropriate, the bacteria, which is well to antibiotics, will develop a bacterium very resistant to antibiotics which will proliferate rapidly in the poor conditions.
In the event of poor provisional or extended by the immune system, this bacteria can cause serious infections, such as a traumatic infection or septicemia, on the elderly patients, small weight or having a weakened body.
According to the doctor manager of the hospital, there is nothing particularly in infections mrsa, these infections are part of the daily hospitals.
Above all, it should not confuse the infection with the epidemic, they do not find mrsa only or they are not sought, has said.
Her resist antibiotics.
"these patients are isolated, nurses puts on rubber and masks and we have antibiotics adapted for the care", has said.
A priori, the in-patients are examined whether they are carrying mrsa, though infection cannot always be avoided.
The sample is not the method
The great majority of infections caused by the mrsa could be warned, but the conditions and the present circumstances are not favourable, in hospitals Hungarians, to prevent the development and the proliferation of pathogenes agents, says to böröcz.
As this infection manifests itself in the hospitals and homes for the elderly, the hospitals should check the in-patients and isolate the ill holders of mrsa immediately.
Nevertheless the microbiological is not the method in the Hungarian hospitals.
It is necessary to know that the national case of social security does not finance these examinations.
The majority of cases sees the light of day that if the infection mrsa is only on the patient, has declared the doctor in leader of the epidemiological centre.
The European Union has relating strict recommendations has adapted to the use of antibiotics in human medicine, and there is also the Hungarian directives for the recovery of certain infections and syndromes.
It must be made so that the antibiotic therapy is targeted, in other words the microbiological examinations should be carried out in order to empecher resistance to the drugs but the hospitals still do not take into account.
The realization of the microbiological is still more rare in the care and in the basic care, böröcz communicated.
Many hospitals do the economy on the disinfectants
The evidence shows that the proliferent a patient has another more often through the medical staff.
It is therefore essential to wash its hands, to put on and masks. However important gaps are detected in the hospitals also in this field.
The proliferent by infection transmitted by inhalation of droplets and contact. However, because of the conditions in the Hungarian hospitals, the patient contaminated cannot always be isolated.
Furthermore, the rooms are often full, beds are often too close some of the others while in terms of epidemic, the patients should be removed some of the other of 1.5 to the minimum.
Unfortunately, we also note that, in a difficult situation, to make savings on the disinfectants, they lack of, the patients are numerous, so the risk of contamination is even greater, pointed out to böröcz.
According to böröcz, in hospitals or preventive measures are respected, the number of infections is weaker demonstrable or even the proliferation of the agent can be blocked.
Governmental plan against the mrsa
The treatment of the infection mrsa represents exorbitant expenditure for the cases of social security, this is why one conflict everywhere against this infection.
In England, for example, the government has established a plan to prevent or reduce the incidence of mrsa.
According to the data published, this agenda is effective and infections mrsa show a tendency decreasing in England.
The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) revealed among its priorities for the prevention of the impact of the pathogenes agents (as the mrsa also) as well as the prevention of infections caused by these agents.
