Additional 400 million euros for the infrastructure
To veres, Hungarian minister of finance, and Marta gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB), have signed, on Friday, Budapest, three agreements to a total value of 400 million euros, concerning a line of credit in order to support the education, infrastructure, transport and the environment, as well as the energy.
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB), has adopted a budget of 300 million euros for the Hungarian budget financing projects in transport and environment has carried out from the Cohesion Fund, where a policy of credit to a value of 100 million euros has been signed by the parties, and this time, the contract signed concerns the use of 200 million euro remaining.
The agreement on the credit of 150 million euros also relates to the budgetary financing projects in education.
The European Investment Bank has approved on the whole a sum of 300 million euros for Hungary, 150 million euro remaining will be able to be used later, following the extension of the contract of credit.
The parties have signed a contract of 50 million euros for innovation, the state budget will use this envelope within the framework of the project of research and development has to realize the University of debrecen.
During the negotiations, the project of the line 4 of the subway has also been discussed.
The parties have agreed that they would the possible modification of the initial contract while Hungary finalizes the details of the financing of the subway with the EU.
According to veres, that could be done in the first quarter of 2008.
Since 1990, the EIB has granted to the whole 8.4 billion euros for the financing of 113 projects in Hungary.
The EIB grants its appropriations according to the rate of related has Euribor, with a grace period of eight years and no Commission commitment.
Bulgaria, paradise of the property market of the EU
The evolution of the Bulgarian property market is spectacular, the attention of all Europe is turned towards the countries of the Balkans little quoted by the past.
What, or and who buys on this market of the EU that is always the least expensive but which will quickly become expensive?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of re.
Currently, in housing, Bulgaria is unquestionably the most fashionable target of Europe with its flats winter and its houses to the seaside cheap.
In the mountains, the most popular areas are bansko, borovec, pamprovo and vitosa and, at the edge of the sea, albéna, "Sands and", the "coast of the sun", the former sozopol and nessebar but they are increasingly numerous has to seek a building in the area of kavarna and balcik also.
According to the analysis of re Bulgaria, sooner or later, the central area of the country, namely veliko tarnovo, gabrovo, Elena, triavna, also wake up the intéret investors, and they are also increasingly numerous has to buy in the corner of very dear to trick.
Sofia, the capital, offer attractive opportunities also, surfaces of trade and offices have the highest rate of redemption.
Bulgaria is on the best way to become one of the most attractive paradise of course of Europe and to be a priority destination, after the summer season and the winter season, also in the other two seasons of the year.
The more vigilant investors buy déja in large numbers, for example in the corner of bansko.
According to the analysis, the people buying a building in Bulgaria look at same time has to change their lives, their way of life.
The majority of the buyers are English but other arrive from France, Belgium, Spain and more in Romania.
The Maltese and Cypriot are also present. By the Black Sea and in the most reputable winter resorts, we traditionally meet many buyers Russian.
The foreign buyers to be divided into three groups, said Georgij jankov, regional director of re Bulgaria.
The people who intend to settle buy the renovated buildings, has a price varying between 50 and 100 thousand euros, or old houses deteriorated, has a price from 5 has 15 thousand euros, which are then renovated.
The criteria are the easy and the possibilities of communication, the proximity of a large city, stores and in general that the local doctor.
The second group understands the purchasers of secondary (since last December, Bulgaria is quoted among the 10 destinations of holidays in Germany).
The third group is made up of commercial investors who buy in the hope of accomplishing a gain a medium or long term.
The price of the buildings of the capital increases constantly due to an increasingly keen demand.
In the European Union, the real prices are the lowest in Bulgaria; however, these 5 years, they have increased by 21% every year.
The increase of property prices is primarily the increase in wages.
