Political capital: the Hungarian guard has increased the risk country
According to the division risk analysis of political capital (risk division), the activity of the Hungarian guard, constituted in August last year, with the support of the jobbik magyarországért mozgalom (movement for a better Hungary) increases, under several aspects, the political risk of Hungary and of the region.
In its "warning of risk", the company announces that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian guard, the greatest political risk is déja that "in the short term ethnic clashes aggressive can occur following the worsening of the ethnic tension déja existing between the population gypsy and not gypsy Hungary".
The research institute has added that the political strategy of the Hungarian guard aiming probably has to cause this situation is the main reason.
As they say, it is one of the main gaps in the Hungarian political actors: "the public actors have crossed the public debate on the matter of the Roma, the representatives of the radical political groupings and which have a political strategy based on the disagreement between the gypsies and the Hungarians."
The problem is some aggravated, the normal dialogue becomes impossible, the extremists have reinforced and the arrival of the aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the influence of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media to the activity of the Hungarian guard "has deteriorated significantly the image of Hungary abroad, in particular concerning the confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They say that, following a greater publicity given the reorganization of the radical groups and Hungarian upright since the autumn of 2006, numerous associations have been constituted in Hungary since the summer 2007 giving the name of "national association of self-defence."
"The common feature of this gathering is that they are defined as a civil organization while they publicly declare the preparation of their members has missions of defence (disasters, national defence, defence force), armed if it is necessary, in addition, by pointing out the disability of the police, the army, in other words the State", added.
They have reported that everything was in accordance with the method which, by relying on the resentment of society and of the political parties, seeks to disguise a different political ambitions under a civil aspect.
The emphasis put on the civil and the statute of association is therefore only that has to avoid the legal rights of the recording of these associations in the Court, but they are also a political strategy.
The analysis signals that the activity of the Hungarian guard is a factor which also increases the risk in relation to the relations of neighbourhood.
"in recent months, many countries quote the Hungarian guard as a potential source of risk and the political actors of some bordering countries wish to justify their political anti-Hungarian in referring to the Constitution of the Hungarian guard.
This influences the political stability of the region, "added.
According to the Institute of research, the Constitution of the Hungarian guard is not a unique in Central Europe, the political risks have increased over the whole of the region.
As they say, the operation of the Hungarian guard looks, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian national guard which the Constitution has been declared by the Bulgarian National Union (bnu) in 2007.
The many confusion of Roma who burst in an area of Sofia (kraszna poljana) are at the origin of the Constitution of the Bulgarian guard.
Taking advantage of these events, bnu decided to constitute a guard in saying that the objective of the organization is national self-defence ".
According to them, these 17 years, Romany "terrorized" Bulgaria but the state has remained inactive and neutral, points out the political capital.
They have added that the initiative had aroused lively debate in the Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the declaration of certain organizations of Roma Bulgarians regarding the constitution of their own guard by way of resistance signals to the increase in the risk of ethnic clashes.
The operation of the Hungarian guard showing similarities with that of the Bulgarian national guard excluded that Roma Hungarian react to the threat in the same way by their own self-defence, they can read in the warning of the risk of political capital.
At the request of the news of the Agency telegraph, Attila juhász, Director of research of political capital, has said: the risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he has said, their risk analysis is published every year and if events occurred which could have an impact on the change of the risk, they inform public opinion, as in the present case, publishing a warning of risk.
