Yesterday, the Ministers of the Czech Government signed in all nine operational programs with representatives of the European Commission, which could, in the years to come, to bring 14 billion euros (about 365 billion Crowns Czech) in the Czech Republic.
It is almost half of the whole of the sum that the Czech Republic can obtain from Brussels in the years 2007 to 2013.
