We are part of the country which, on a global scale, are threatened by poverty.
We have therefore no need for massive social programs which, precisely in the last few years, unfortunately unnecessarily.
Although they succeed in eliminating a part of the absurd populist expenditure, approved last year before the elections, if a shift of the age limit for retirement, so that a reform of the pension system will not take place soon, then all policy will cease to exist in that country, and anyone who is in power, it will be only to manage.
