This is the reason why the current budget cannot be revolutionary, but it can only suspend the mechanism that fact that the ordinary expenses are rejected by the expenses of mandates.
The deficit of 70 billion scheduled for 2008 will be absolutely useless if the previous governments had not dispelled all the money that they could.
If we really do not want it to happen that the policies to be able to become simple bureaucrats, it is necessary for us to be patient and to grant this coalition government fragile, aware that the state cannot spend that the equivalent of this that it manages to take in taxes and tax laws, the necessary calm to the preparation of new laws of reform.
It is that these latter that will make it possible to reach a balanced state budget progressively.
