The banks to want to regulate the crisis
The American Federal Reserve Bank, the European Central Bank and the central banks English, Switzerland and Canadian have decided to fight together the crisis of the financial markets.
More than one hundred billion dollars will thus be placed on the money markets by the bid.
It will be a matter for the banks to sell, by a system of bids, the interest rate they are ready to borrow money.
By way of example, the American EDF will send auction 40 billion dollars, and, furthermore, it will provide 24 billion to the European Central Bank and Switzerland.
This is the first time since the attacks of September that the central banks of individual States have decided on a concerted action at this point, to prevent or reduce the effects of the financial crisis.
"this move tends to regulate the major problems of the economy, that is to say the increasing lack of free capital that banks could lend ', writes in his report to the customers Bernard baumohl society of Council economic group.
"the joint action of the central banks has reduced the likelihood of a recession in the United States from 65% to around 50%", adds baumohl in his report.
The banks have already lost 60 billion dollars because of the loans not refunded, especially in the United States.
The analysts await further losses of billions.
"if the central banks have chosen this step, it is that they should actually understand what can still be", known as the chief economist of ABN AMRO Davies.
"It appears that the situation is really bad", it adds.
The central banks fear that, if the banks will have a difficult access to loans, they will be more expensive to their customers.
This would reduce the consumption and plunge the American economy in recession that can have an influence on the economic growth of the entire world.
The central banks have made this choice after one has not managed to lower the rate of London, called libor, used to take on the market.
This meant that the banks always feared the mutual loans, even though the American, Canadian and English central banks have reduced on several occasions, during the autumn, their interest rates.
"it will have the same effect as a new lower rates of interest", said to the Agency Reuters Greg salvaggio society Tempus consulting.
Certain analysts do not believe that the step of the central banks will not contribute to avert the crisis, since it does not regulate the main problem which is the fall of the property market to the USA.
