In Afghanistan, the allies are passive, affirm the Americans
The lack of soldiers and equipment necessary influences, according to the United States, on the progress of the mission in Afghanistan.
According to the Defence Minister Robert gates, NATO should sketch a concrete plan for the years to come.
The mission in Afghanistan does not proceed as it should, agreed at Edinburgh in Scotland the representatives of countries which have troops in the southern part of the country.
Next to the increasing protest on the part of the Taliban movement, the eight States involved also discuss today future plans and the coordination of the allies.
While the United States have called this week through the Defence Minister Robert gates NATO troops to a greater activity, the United Kingdom sees as priority the reinforcement of the authority of the Afghan Government and the enhancement of development aid.
"the trend in Afghanistan is perceptible, but the military power can constitute only a part of the solution.
The other is to allow the people to start a new development of the economy and of the security ", said in the chain BBC Defence Minister of Browne.
Ninety percent
The activity of the Afghan insurgents is, according to the data of the American army, the more intense the past five years.
The number of violent actions has increased by 27% in comparison with last year, up to 60% in the province, located in the south of the country.
NATO countries have approximately 40 thousand soldiers in Afghanistan, which nearly a quarter in the southern part.
However, according to the United States, the allies have reached their absolute limit and in the organization and the equipment of troops.
In concrete terms, they ask other helicopters, soldiers and experts to drive of the troops.
"We will have to reflect seriously on the concrete objectives for the coming period, as well as on the ways how to reach", said gates.
The Secretary General of NATO de Hoop held today similar.
"I am not happy with what we have on the ground and in the air in Afghanistan.
We have more or less Ninety percent of the soldiers and equipment which we would need, and this is not enough, "said Hoop at the Agency Reuters at the end of the talks with the Japanese Government in Tokyo which lasted three days.
That is passive
These last months reign equally between the countries involved in conflicts concerning the question whether all the allies do indeed all their possible in Afghanistan.
For example, Germany has been criticized for passivity.
"the Germans have a relatively numerous representation in Afghanistan.
But they are engaged in areas where violence is minimal, combat the requirements to which they are subject, therefore, are not as strict as those in the south and the east of the country where we operate, "said gates.
The tabloid britanique sun has described this week the German soldiers lazy.
"The Afghan discovered: the Germans play, while ours fight", has written sun in a document supplemented by photographs of German soldiers playing to the table.
The German newspaper Bild is passed to the counter-attack in publishing the picture of a troop during a game of rugby in the southern part of Afghanistan.
