The total debt brought up, at the end of September, to 842.7 billion Crowns.
The government had planned to borrow 159,2 billion Crowns this year.
Thanks to an evolution of the economies of the budget of the State better than expected, the Ministry has reduced the amount envisaged in 152.8 billion Crowns.
The debt of the State of the Czech Republic has gone up to the end of the month of September to 842.7 billion Crowns.
During the nine months of this year it has increased 40,2 billion Crowns.
However, from the month of June, it has reduced from 13.4 billion Crowns.
