The debts grow
The national debt is constituted by the debts of the central government and it is mainly generated by the cumulation of the deficits of the budget of the State.
The national debt is financed by the Treasury, government bonds, direct loans or by example by loans to the European Investment Bank.
The internal debt of the State increased this year for the moment of 38.5 billion to 719.4 billion Crowns.
The external debt of the State has increased this year for the moment of 1.7 billion Crowns to 123.3 billion Crowns.
The debt of the state called negotiable reached at the end of September 803.3 billion Crowns and from the month of June it has reduced 13,7 billion Crowns.
The average of the national debt rose in years.
