Now, at the beginning of September, thanks to an evolution of the economies of the budget of the State better than expected, the Ministry has reduced the amount envisaged in 152,8 billion Crowns.
The sum is mainly made up by the deficit of the budget of the state which will obviously obviousness 76 billion Crowns this year, instead of the 91.3 billion Crowns initially envisaged.
Secondly, it is a matter of sources foreseen for the job of strengthening the Czech, namely 13,3 billion Crowns, the reservation of 10 billion for the payment of retirement, the financing of the government bonds of State for 43 billion Crowns and of the loans from the European Investment Bank coming to 1.8 billion Crowns.
