The tension is rising in Pakistan
The police suppressed the first demonstrations on Monday for the establishment of the state of emergency two days ago by the General Musharraf.
In the city of Lahore, in the east of the country, about 2,000 lawyers who demonstrated against the measures taken in the framework of the state of emergency, have been injured by the tear grenades used by the forces of order, according to witnesses.
The latter counteracted by their government, injuring police officers.
At least 350 lawyers have been challenged.
Similar scenarios in Karachi and Rawalpindi, or the police officers responsible and injured lawyers.
One would have been challenged.
In Islamabad, the lawyers of the bar of the Supreme Court called for a general strike and announced demonstrations, following a wave of about 500 arrests during the weekend of political opponents, human rights activists and lawyers.
The streets leading to the Supreme Court were blocked on Monday morning to prevent the Union.
Other demonstrations have taken place in multan (centre) and in Peshawar (north-west).
The movement of lawyers gathered on Monday the support of religious parties grouped together in the powerful alliance Muttahida majlis-e-amal "which the President urged the population to send flowers to the judges who are decided against the state of emergency and refuse to those who have lent oath before Musharraf".
"The promise of Musharraf does not hold any more"
The High Court is aimed directly by the extent of emergency proclaimed on Saturday evening.
It was to decide in the next few days on the legality of the re-election to the presidential election, on 6 October, to the indirect vote, President Musharraf.
The President of the Court, tried Mohammed Chaudhry, has been ousted and replaced.
"all this to which we are witnessing is illegal, and contrary to the judgments of the Court," said the magistrate in the newspaper the news.
The promise of pervez Musharraf to leave the head of the army and become a civilian President "does not take more" after the introduction of the state of emergency, has said on Monday the - information Tariq azeem.
That it abandons its military uniform was given by 15 November, dates back to the end of its first term.
The - the information has also confirmed that the January elections could be deferred.
Moreover, the government has denied pressing rumours in the country according to which the President Musharraf would have been assigned to residence by his assistant Chief of the armed forces.
