This calculation takes into account the unwanted pregnancies (24%), as well as the poorly planned births or arising in an unexpected way.
Even today, more than a pregnancy on three (36%) is not envisaged, reveals a study conducted by the National Institute of demographic studies (ined), forty years after the vote of the law neuwirth that liberalized contraception in France.
This calculation takes into account the unwanted pregnancies (24%), as well as the poorly planned births or arising in an unexpected way.
The various methods of contraception as the pill or the coil still show a rate of failure of 5% to 6%, values ined.
