Spectacular repair on the space station
It has taken more than seven hours of work in the space to the astronaut Scott parazynski and his friends of the crew of the international space station (simple percentages) to carry out the spectacular repairing a solar panel torn, essential to the pursuit of the scientific activities of the station.
A risky exit that has accumulated records because of its duration, its removal from the modules, the speed with which it has been imagined, tools "fixed" by the astronauts for carrying out the repair.
The problem has appeared on Tuesday while the astronauts had discharged from the shuttle the unit, a big part in charge of welcoming soon the European and Japanese scientific laboratories (see supervised).
This unit is a kind of quay of for the.
But it is necessary to be able to supply them with electricity.
The second task of the crew was therefore move a unit of production of electricity by solar panels weighing 17.5 tonnes, already present on the simple percentages, in order to put to post on its final position.
After moving, the crew has started the redeployment of solar panels of the unit which have a scale of 76 metres.
And it is here that one of the signs, which are as accordions, has been damaged on nearly half a metre by a cable which has jammed.
The deployment has been halted, not to harm the panel more.
The astronauts who originally had to carry out an exit of control of the Shuttle, then to go to make up for another solar panel which the rotation system was defective, were forced to devote itself to the damaged sign.
And this is Scott parazynski that has been chosen to go ahead at the end of the 30 metres in length of the arm of the shuttle added to that of the station to perform repair.
This is one of the best "spacewalker" (space Walker) NASA.
Large, resistant, very skilful, it has developed and the very long arm.
To 46 years, this doctor of training has therefore been responsible "operating" the solar panel "injured".
After precisely to have inspected damage, it has divided the cable and installed sorts of "hitch" on the damaged zone.
It was helped by a second "spacewalker" remained near the lock and, from the inside, by other astronauts which Peggy whitson, the crew.
The tool that he has used, a minicanne hockey wrapped insulating material to avoid electrocution on solar panels producing several hundred volts, has been conceived "and" arranged by the astronauts at the edge of the station.
Once the operation ended, Scott parazynski given that the panel is entirely unfolded before making an inventory of the tools and regain the inside of the station.
Yesterday afternoon, the astronauts took advantage of a day of rest before today, seven astronauts regain the shuttle for a return on earth envisaged on Wednesday.
The title EADS sanctioned in stock market
The action EADS is going down currently in Paris, after the group of aeronautics and defence has announced that it was going to have to spend between 1.2 and 1.4 billion euros to face up to the delays of l.
EADS loses 4% to 21.96 euros in Paris.
The group was obliged to revise its forecasting of operational result for 2007 further delays caused by the slow progress of the development of the engine of L, which conditions the inauguration theft of the plane.
The cost to compensate for the delay in the delivery of its of military transport aircraft, announced in October, amounts "between 1.2 and 1.4 billion euros, which more than 1 billion for Airbus", has announced the headquarters of the European EADS.
Because of these contributions, EADS will be forced to announce new objectives of turnover (ebit) for 2007 during the presentation of its quarterly results next Thursday, it adds without more precision.
The group also points out that the appraisal of the new expenses is consistent with the delay of six months.
As a reminder, the operational result of EADS has fallen to 86% in 2006, mainly because of expenses related to the delays of another issue, that of the very large transport aircraft.
Initially, the group envisaged the first delivery of L in the French army in October 2009.
The choice of the status quo
There will be no suspense, on Sunday, at the exit polls: the Russians are going to opt for the party of President Putin, United Russia.
Confirming their aspiration to stability, or even to the authoritarianism, after a very locked campaign.
Three days of the legislative elections, the Russian President Vladimir Putin sends a message today to the voters televised on public channels, already recorded but whose contents are kept secret.
It is as a list of Russia united, the party of which the victory looks to be enormous.
Yesterday, the President has nothing showed in accepting the foreign ambassadors, be satisfied to deliver a new charge against the West, accused of interference - its theme of preference for the country.
"We know the price of a true democracy and wish the honest elections, more transparent and more open, elections without tears," he added.
In the eyes of the opposition, one is.
It reports a campaign tainted with pressures.
The Communist leader guennadi ziouganov says that there has never been elections as "dirty, even at the time of Yeltsin."
After the repression of demonstrations of last weekend, the ex-world world of failures Garry Kasparov, sentenced to five days of prison for illegal demonstration, remains prohibited visit according to his lawyer.
"the Russians have kept the mentality of the homosexual"
Behind these legislative without suspense out two issues much more open.
- which will succeed in Putin to the Presidency?
The Official Journal published the date of the first round of the presidential election, on 2 March 2008; the candidates have until 23 December to be made known.
Elected in 2000 and re-elected in 2004, Vladimir Putin can aspire to a third consecutive mandate.
Yet no successor emerges.
- what role will Putin after March?
Prime Minister?
Leader of the parliamentary majority and the all-powerful party United Russia who choose the government and the President?
At all events, with legislative and presidential election, the power will triumph.
This is a tradition.
"the Russians have kept the mentality of the homosexual, they do not feel masters of their own destiny," considers the sociologist lev goudkov, Director of the independent centre levada.
This kopossov Nikolaï, of the University of state of Saint Petersburg, goes back further: civil society has fallen behind in this country five centuries after Europe; the famous Community spirit has delayed the formation of the individualism.
After the liberal reforms of the nineties, "Putin again with the model of a paternalistic state, perfectly accepted by the population of much more than this new paternalism has not been followed by terror, but by a certain economic wealth, Maria lipman estimates, the Carnegie Foundation.
Today the Russians "renounce willingly personal responsibility" which they had fixed shown after the break-up of the USSR.
Why to think? "
The phenomenon affects all social strata, including the business world.
And the administrative elite intends to preserve the status quo: 65 governors (on 85 heads of Russian regions) direct the local lists of Russia united.
The new freedoms imported from the West is often synonymous with chaos, as in the nineties.
The opinion prefers the stability.
In the name of what the Russians not vote for the extremists.
Conclusion of Tamara tcherednitchenko, Professor: why think?
Those who are in power are not too bad, why change? "
A heavy memory
After more than 60 years of confidentiality, the Nazi archives of bad arolsen, which relate to the fates of 17.5 million victims of the system, are in free access.
The 47 million archive documents, stored on 27 km of linear in bad arolsen (Hesse), were not so far only with a goal "humanitarian", that is to say in an individual and personal way, on request of an old victim or of its rightful claimants.
The eleven states in charge of their management - Germany, France, Israel and the United States agreed in May 2006 to open to the researchers and historians.
The process of ratification of the agreement by all the States being completed, openness is effective since yesterday.
Sensitive information
The access of historians to bad arolsen will make it possible to carry out investigations "in particular on the movements of prisoners, the population of the camps and the health of the workers forced", is reto meistern, the director of these files managed by the International Committee of the Red Cross ().
Until recently, a number of States, including Germany, opposed to opening up to the public of the personal documents, because of the sensitive nature of some information.
As the supposed homosexuality or mental disability of certain victims of deportation.
The registers of the concentration camps or of the arrest warrant established by the Gestapo had been gathered after war in a practical purpose: to find the civil prisoners or subject to obligatory work and, if required, to bring a proof of their internment, in order to open the way to their compensation.
Even today in bad arolsen, more than 300 permanent employees treat tens of thousands of individual requests.
However, for a part of the scientific community, access to bad arolsen takes on a limited interest.
There is nothing basically again to wait for these documents, "said in 2006 the Wolfgang Benz, Director of the research centre on anti-Semitism in the universität of Berlin.
The EU and India want to reach an agreement of free trade in 2008
Currently, the bilateral trade is already close to 60 billion euros per annum.
The EU is the largest trading partner of India and accounts for 18% of its foreign trade.
The European Union and India hope to sign an agreement of free trade in 2008, pointed out the European Commissioner in trade, Peter Mandelson and its Indian counterpart, Kamal Nath.
The Foreign Ministers of the EU had given in last April the green light to the European Commission to start negotiations with a view to signing agreements of free trade (FTA) with India, South Korea and the Association of South East Asian Nations (ASEAN) .le bilateral trade is already close to 60 billion euros per annum.
The EU is the largest trading partner of India and accounts for 18% of its foreign trade.
Read is also its first foreign investor, but India is only the 9th trading partner of the EU, according to the figures of the European Commission.
"a pact of free trade will dope the two economies" and "India would improve its access to a market of 450 million Europeans prosperous", justified Peter Mandelson.
Europe represents the first or the second market for each of the first ten products exported by India, has clarified the European Commissioner giants Asian and European exchange annually for "47 billion euros of goods" and "ten billion euros of services", said this week Danièle smadja, leader of the delegation of the European Commission in New Delhi, regretting that the bilateral trade "did not yet reached its potential" .l EU and India can be found on Friday to their eighth diplomatic Summit in New Delhi Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and the President of the European Commission, José Manuel Barroso.
