Following many rumours about the creation, by C3, of a new music festival in Philadelphia, the promoter / producer announces the vineland music festival in New Jersey, in partnership with Republic festival of British producer melvin Benn.
"for our business, it is an honour to work with a person who, neither more nor less, inspired the current movement festival in America," entrusted Charlie Jones of C3 to
C3 produces the festival of Chicago and Austin city music festival.
Vineland, to the New Jersey, is a summer destination for the camp-site.
The festival should be held from 8 to 10 August on a farm deprived of 500 acres with about 40 minutes of Philadelphia.
Formerly known under the name of fiddler, the director of festival Republic, melvin Benn, is one of the producers of festivals more respected in the world.
In 1989, he has taken the bar of reading festival in the United Kingdom, which attracts some 80 000 people annually.
In 1999, melvin Benn added Leeds festival in his portfolio and then, in 2006, festival Republic has created the latitude festival of henham park in Suffolk.
Since 2002, by way of a flat melvin Benn is also responsible for the production, the concession of licences and organizational tasks of the glastonbury festival, who can now receive 177 500 people.
Describing glastonbury of "event more inspiring" which it ever attended, Charlie Jones of C3 said that his firm and that of melvin Benn work in parallel to give to the region a festival event of European style.
"We had chosen Philadelphia as market and worked diligently with fairmount parks Commission to create a festival in the area of Philadelphia", Charlie Jones supports.
"We were in talks with the city and the Commission was justified and filled with enthusiasm for this project.
Unfortunately, we are stuck in politicailleries because the present administration, follows Charlie Jones.
", fortunately, we have been able to discuss with melvin Benn and we are on the point of creating a superb festival on an exceptional site which, ultimement, will serve as the population of Philadelphia."
C3 has revived the festival in 2005 to grant Park of Chicago, after distancing itself in the festival landscape in 2002 with the Austin city music festival.
The two events have recorded respective gross earnings of $and $in 2007.
These two festivals are held in urban environment.
"The European model of melvin Benn is a festival, while ours take place in urban green spaces," said Charlie Jones.
The objective is to merge, in one way or another, the two formulas to give at the same time an impression of festival in the European and urban to American. "
Vineland is almost halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The Community of vineland, including the mayor, support with enthusiasm the behaviour of this event," said Charlie Jones.
This last refuses to reveal the terms of the agreement, but says "that they are sufficiently interesting to make it possible to invest in such an event and to receive a festival, let us hope, will have a long life.
Charlie Jones says that the capacity of reception of this festival is "very great", like that of 80 000 people of bonnaroo music festival in tennessee.
It says that invitations have been launched in the groups, but that nothing could still be confirmed at the moment to go in the press.
"vineland will be at rock, but the music will be varied, in the hope of attracting all kinds of spectators," said Charlie Jones.
Its partners of C3, which has received the prize top independent promoter of the last billboard awards, are Charlie Walker and Charles Attal.
