My doctor doctor has talked to me one of its articles on research strange entitled: 'the money product cerebral, especially if the others receive less'.
That is to say, that the feelings that generates the pay of workers monthly depends on what the colleagues win.
The study has been carried out through the magnetic resonance in the University of Bonn, and the results are published in the last number of science.
According to Bernd Weber, author of the study and manager of the group in charge of the images of neurocognition of life & brain Institute, in Germany: "the strongest activation occurred when the participant replied correctly and his companion failed".
Researchers have noticed that when the two people that they received the same pay, activity was moderate, but if one of them accepted the double, activity was greater.
I do not know if this conclusion required so many science.
