The Ministry of Health will have to carry out checks meadow job on the staff overseas, to be sure of the validity of their skills, experiences, and work permits for the United Kingdom.
Although the Scottish Ministry of Health use disclosure to carry out the controls of criminal precedents, the Agency has no right to obtain such information out of the United Kingdom.
Among the many warnings, the report of the general now says that the committees are required to be confronted with the office of control of criminal precedents, thus allowing the employers to undertake checks on various countries.
"Well that we have discovered that some information regarding the staff have been proved, it is made every time" announces the report.
Mr black has declared that the Scottish Ministry of Health checks pre carries out most of the jobs that it would make itself, but it has also added: "our report throws into relief aspects where the system can be improved in order to ensure that adequate information on certain members of the overseas personnel are available to the medical services.
Mr Peter Terry, President of bma Scotland has declared that it is highly unlikely that the "" controls meadow employment can identify the workers likely to make future terrorist acts.
It says, "the report suggests that the checks carried out presently, work well in the Scottish health system and that it is not certain that these warnings can bring about added value.
The Scottish health authorities have declared to use 1161 people overseas, made up for the most part of doctors and nurses.
