The climate of Venus could be the future of the earth.
The scientists have yesterday said that Venus has certainly been a pleasant planet to live.
The data coming from the European vessel in orbit showed that the planet is certainly two times smaller than the earth, contrary to what we thought beforehand.
Venus is the planet more closely to the land.
These two worlds are practically the same size, with similar orbits Venus, well that is closer to the sun.
The scientists believe now that there are billions of years, Venus could have had conditions similar to those of the earth, and could even have been living.
But the greenhouse effect due to the carbon dioxide, the atmospheric erosion in solar expulsions at a slower rotation Venus has led to a different kind of development.
Today the planet is deprived of water, devastated by hurricanes and storms of lightning and has a surface temperature warm enough to melt lead.
The findings of come express, the of the European Space Agency, which has studied the planet for one year, offers a sad vision of the future potential of the earth due to the disastrous effects of climate changes.
The teacher of the Department of physical appearance of the University of Oxford, Fred Taylor, one of the leaders of the mission of the come express, said: "we begin to understand why the climate of Venus is so different from that of the earth, although planets in them even are virtually similar.
"our new data enable us to establish a scenario according to which there are billions of years, Venus originally would have been the same as the earth, can be even with a living space.
