Frauds of cards.
The crisis of mortgages contaminate the American market of credit cards?
When there is the blood in water, it is normal to see fins, whirl around.
Now that the US housing market runs through a critical phase, the predatory aim to the American market of credit cards.
The analysts from goldman Sachs, think that the losses linked to the credit cards could reach $99 billion if the contagion stretches of mortgages in other forms of credit to the consumer.
Signs of tension are clearly visible.
There are increases in rates of expenses and insolvency, what measures the parts of the assessment or which are, more than 30 days afterwards.
Hsbc announced last month that it has taken $1.4 billion in its appropriations to the consumer, in part because of the weakness of the holders of cards.
It is still too early to panic.
The expenses and are still moderate.
According to moody, a tax agency, the rate of insolvency of 3.89% of the troixième term is inferior almost a point in relation to its historical average.
The deterioration of the rates is partly explainable by technical factors.
A change in the law in 2005 in the United States, concerning the personal bankruptcy has caused an abrupt fall of the files of bankruptcy, which in turn caused heavy losses for credit cards; the number of files (and therefore of rates of insolvency) could increase even if the conditions of loans were to get worse.
The industry announced in addition to the fixed rates of payment, which highlight the sum of monthly debt that consumers need to regulate.
And the confidence in the sureté of the capital of credit cards is strong enough, despite the paralysis of other aspects of the structured finance.
Dennis moroney of towergroup, a society of research, predicted that the volume of emission for 2007 will be 25% higher than last year.
The direct links of infection amongst the crisis of mortgages and the market of credit cards indeed exist: the consumers would prefer to increase their debts now that equitable real loans have disappeared.
But the transmitters of cards pay more attention to the flow of cash rather than to the value of the heritage, and therefore the fall in the prices of the property has inevitably led to a change in the credibility of the borrowers.
They could even bring benefits to the transmitters of titles of credit.
The premiums to the consumers for the payment of mortgages fall if ownership costs less than the value of the loan, by consequence, the debt by credit card would become a priority to pay the whole again.
The transmitters of cards are able to respond much more rapidly than the ones and with more flexibility in such conditions of crisis, because they can change the interest rates or alter the limits of rédit.
It should in theory to reduce the risk of having a quick return of actions.
"We are not going to wake up one morning and to re-examine all the loans has declared Gary perlin, the director of one capital.
If a financial disaster of the market of credit cards is unlikely, there is a strong risk of having a consequent decrease.
If the lower prices of real estate and shrinkage in the credit market bring us to the recession, the industry will have to face a macabre future.
