Venus is the infernal of the earth.
In spite of its atmosphere hostile to the life, Venus looks more like the earth that what they believed until now: the European space "come express" discovered lightning in the atmosphere and of the wind in the Poles, similar to those which appear in the winter on earth.
For almost three decades, the scientists assume that there are flashes on Venus.
The European "come express" has now brought the proof - it has detected electromagnetic waves in the limit of the atmosphere: flashes on Venus burst at a height of around 56 kilometres of all in all, brings back Christopher de the University of California in Los Angeles in the scientific journal "nature".
According to the famous theory of the cyprine, lightning would have revealed the life on earth: the storm would have stimulated reactions in the oceans which have led to the formation of amino acids, stone of the way of life.
This is not the case on Venus: "If life there has been, it must have been a very old date of history ', explains Solomon" Carnegie institution "in Washington.
It should be today hardly living things to the surface of Venus: the atmosphere is approximately one hundred times more dense that on earth, it is sometimes temperatures of 500 degrees.
"Venus is perhaps the infernal of the earth, but it remains a twin", said russel.
Why Venus, which looks so much to the land masses and dimensions, has been struck an evolution so different, is the fundamental question of the mission.
The departure of "come express" in November 2005 was an important step in the research, since no more probe was bound to the exploration of this planet since the eighties ten.
In the opinion of the scientists, the most recent research results that have now been introduced in several articles of "nature" do not point out not only the oddity of Venus within the solar system.
They also show that the mutual interests with the earth from our neighbouring are more than assumed in the first place.
So the researchers have found, in addition to the wind known to the North Pole, a pole of clouds in the South, which is even more quickly.
The phenomenon of the drafts in the land hemispheres in winter, wrote a team of researchers around Giuseppe piccioni of Istituto Di spaziale e Italian.
The second of the solar has almost the same mass that the earth and is, with a diameter of 12,100 measure the mileage, almost as great.
The qualified star of the evening or the morning revolves around the sun in just 225 days.
It is however much more slowly on itself: a hard day 243 days land.
Although Venus, with temperatures in the surface of 460 degrees Celsius and a pressure of 92 bar, recalls the earth, the scientists assume that both were formed in similar conditions.
On the two, the water is up and remained on the ground in the form of oceans, but got lost in the space on Venus.
And while the carbon dioxide is fixed on earth in the form of carbonate, it is on Venus the greater part of the atmosphere.
